Blocks.Text: Pursuant to this prospectus supplement and the accompanying prospectus, we are offering 14,414,370 shares of our common
stock to Azimuth Opportunity, L.P., or Azimuth, pursuant to a Common Stock Purchase Agreement, dated November 8, 2011, between
us and Azimuth, at a price of approximately $1.73 per share. The total purchase price for the shares is $25.0 million. We will receive
net proceeds from the sale of these shares of approximately $24.7 million after deducting our estimated offering expenses of
approximately $0.3 million, including a placement agent fee of $187,500 to be paid to Reedland Capital Partners, an Institutional
Division of Financial West Group, in connection with this offering.
This prospectus supplement and the accompanying prospectus also cover the sale of these shares by Azimuth to the public.
Azimuth is an “underwriter” within the meaning of Section 2(a)(11) of the Securities Act of 1933, as amended, and any profits on the
sales of shares of our common stock by Azimuth and any discounts, commissions or concessions received by Azimuth may be deemed
to be underwriting discounts and commissions under the Securities Act.
